      <title>Introduction to Embedded Systems with Docker</title>
      <link>http://localhost:1313/blog/introduction-embedded-systems-docker/</link>
      <pubDate>Tue, 30 Apr 2024 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate>
      <guid>http://localhost:1313/blog/introduction-embedded-systems-docker/</guid>
      <description>&lt;p&gt;Hi everyone joining the course &lt;a href=&#34;https://www.coursera.org/learn/introduction-embedded-systems/home/welcome&#34; target=&#34;_blank&#34; rel=&#34;noreferrer&#34;&gt;Introduction to Embedded Systems Software and Development Environments&lt;/a&gt; on Coursera. I found that installing VirtualBox according to the &lt;a href=&#34;https://www.coursera.org/learn/introduction-embedded-systems/resources/jDf20&#34; target=&#34;_blank&#34; rel=&#34;noreferrer&#34;&gt;suggestion&lt;/a&gt; required downloading a large file and setting up the environment. Instead, I am sharing the steps to set up the environment for the course using Docker.&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;h2 id=&#34;step-1-install-docker&#34; class=&#34;relative group&#34;&gt;Step 1: Install Docker &lt;span class=&#34;absolute top-0 w-6 transition-opacity opacity-0 -start-6 not-prose group-hover:opacity-100&#34;&gt;&lt;a class=&#34;group-hover:text-primary-300 dark:group-hover:text-neutral-700&#34; style=&#34;text-decoration-line: none !important;&#34; href=&#34;#step-1-install-docker&#34; aria-label=&#34;Anchor&#34;&gt;#&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;&lt;p&gt;Get &lt;a href=&#34;https://docs.docker.com/desktop/&#34; target=&#34;_blank&#34; rel=&#34;noreferrer&#34;&gt;Docker Desktop&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;h2 id=&#34;step-2-pull-and-run-the-docker-image&#34; class=&#34;relative group&#34;&gt;Step 2: Pull and run the Docker image &lt;span class=&#34;absolute top-0 w-6 transition-opacity opacity-0 -start-6 not-prose group-hover:opacity-100&#34;&gt;&lt;a class=&#34;group-hover:text-primary-300 dark:group-hover:text-neutral-700&#34; style=&#34;text-decoration-line: none !important;&#34; href=&#34;#step-2-pull-and-run-the-docker-image&#34; aria-label=&#34;Anchor&#34;&gt;#&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;&lt;pre tabindex=&#34;0&#34;&gt;&lt;code&gt;$ docker run -d  ubuntu:22.04 sleep 8640000&#xA;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;h2 id=&#34;step-3-access-the-docker-containe&#34; class=&#34;relative group&#34;&gt;Step 3: Access the Docker containe &lt;span class=&#34;absolute top-0 w-6 transition-opacity opacity-0 -start-6 not-prose group-hover:opacity-100&#34;&gt;&lt;a class=&#34;group-hover:text-primary-300 dark:group-hover:text-neutral-700&#34; style=&#34;text-decoration-line: none !important;&#34; href=&#34;#step-3-access-the-docker-containe&#34; aria-label=&#34;Anchor&#34;&gt;#&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;&lt;pre tabindex=&#34;0&#34;&gt;&lt;code&gt;$ docker container ls&#xA;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;p&gt;You will see the container ID and the name of the container. Use the container ID to access the container.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
